s%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhousing-market-trends-analysis-us-homes-smaller-prices-still-high-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eboth%20smaller%20and%20more%20expensive%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20those%20built%20thirteen%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.census.gov%2Fconstruction%2Fnrc%2Fpdf%2Fquarterly_starts_completions.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECensus%20data%3C%2Fa%3E%20shows%20that%20in%20the%20first%20quarter%20of%202024%2C%20the%20average%20size%20of%20single-family%20homes%20was%202%2C351%20square%20feet%2C%20the%20smallest%20since%20the%20third%20quarter%20of%202009.%20It's%20down%20from%20a%20peak%20of%202%2C736%20square%20feet%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffred.stlouisfed.org%2Fseries%2FHOUSTSFLAA1FQ%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ein%20the%20first%20quarter%20of%202015%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20cost%20to%20buy%20a%20typical%20house%20has%20gone%20up%2082.9%25%20over%20the%20same%20time%20period%2C%20from%20%24197%2C433%20in%20September%202015%20to%20%24361%2C072%20in%20June%202024%2C%20according%20to%20data%20from%20Zillow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20cost%20of%20building%20homes%20has%20also%20grown%20substantially.%20According%20to%20data%20from%20the%20National%20Association%20of%20Home%20Builders%2C%20the%20average%20permit%20value%20for%20single-family%20homes%20has%20risen%20by%2053.2%25%20since%202010.%20This%20figure%20includes%20all%20construction%20costs%2C%20excluding%20land%20and%20lot%20expenses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFacing%20higher%20costs%20for%20building%20materials%20and%20real%20estate%2C%20many%20builders%20are%20downsizing%20their%20projects%20to%20make%20them%20more%20affordable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20July%202024%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjbrec.com%2Finsights%2Fsmaller-home-designs-no-hallways-more-flex-space-nooks%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esurvey%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20John%20Burns%20Research%20and%20Consulting%20(JBREC)%2C%20which%20polled%20300%20residential%20architects%2C%20designers%2C%20and%20design-oriented%20builders%2C%20found%20that%2043%25%20of%20respondents%20worked%20on%20smaller%20projects%20in%202023%20than%20the%20previous%20year%2C%20while%20only%2015%25%20took%20on%20slightly%20larger%20projects.%20Additionally%2C%20on%20average%2C%2027%25%20of%20respondents%20downsized%20their%20projects%20last%20year%20to%20save%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20homeowners%20and%20builders%20make%20tough%20design%20choices%2C%20hallways%20are%20disappearing%20from%20many%20newly%20built%20homes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMikaela%20Arroyo%2C%20vice%20president%20of%20the%20New%20Home%20Trends%20Institute%20at%20JBREC%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20builders%20and%20architects%20are%20instead%20%26quot%3BTetris-ing%20functional%20rooms%20together%2C%26quot%3B%20such%20as%20bedrooms%20and%20living%20rooms%2C%20to%20reduce%20wasted%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimply%20put%2C%20every%20inch%20matters.%20To%20compensate%20for%20smaller%20homes%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Emany%20builders%20sacrifice%20what%20they%20call%20circulation%20spaces%3A%20areas%20that%20aren't%20necessarily%20lived%20in%20but%20connect%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eessential%20rooms%20like%20kitchens%2C%20bathrooms%2C%20and%20bedrooms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20approach%20is%20part%20of%20a%20strategy%20to%20maximize%20usable%20space%20as%20American%20homes%20continue%20to%20shrink.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHomes%20are%20becoming%20slightly%20smaller%20to%20enhance%20affordability%2C%20but%20people%20increasingly%20require%20more%20functionality%20in%20their%20living%20spaces%2C%26quot%3B%20Arroyo%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20also%20a%20sign%20of%20the%20way%20we%20live%20now.%20We%20favor%20open%20floor%20plans%20and%20great%20rooms%20while%20minimizing%20the%20number%20small%20spaces%20blocked%20off%20from%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20house.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222e45f9db-650a-4467-b8df-3ecfe31c175c%5C%22%3EHomebuilders%20are%20prioritizing%20spaces%20that%20get%20used%20most%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETaylor%20Morrison%20and%20Tri%20Pointe%20Homes%2C%20two%20of%20the%20largest%20homebuilders%20in%20the%20US%2C%20are%20among%20the%20companies%20constructing%20fewer%20hallways%2C%20Forbes%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.forbes.com%2Fsites%2Fjamiegold%2F2024%2F07%2F09%2Fwhat-explains-the-new-incredible-shrinking-hallway-space-trend%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20earlier%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20is%20Texas-based%20builder%20Highland%20Homes.%20The%20almost%2040-year-old%20company%20builds%20nearly%204%2C000%20homes%20a%20year%20across%20major%20metropolitan%20areas%2C%20including%20Dallas-Fort%20Worth%2C%20Houston%2C%20Austin%2C%20and%20San%20Antonio.%20Its%20current%20portfolio%20includes%20more%20than%20150%20floor%20plans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJen%20Shurtleff%2C%20director%20of%20product%20research%20and%20development%20at%20Highland%20Homes%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20about%2060%25%20of%20the%20company's%20top%2050%20floor%20plans%20have%20limited%20hallway%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHallways%20are%20often%20seen%20as%20'wasted%20space%2C'%20so%20designers%20are%20moving%20toward%20open%20floor%20plans%20or%20multifunctional%20areas%20that%20flow%20seamlessly%20between%20rooms%2C%26quot%3B%20Shurtleff%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20explained%20that%20a%20hallway%20can%20serve%20as%20a%20multifunctional%20space%20in%20various%20ways.%20For%20example%2C%20if%20it%20connects%20bedrooms%2C%20it%20can%20include%20a%20study%20area%20with%20a%20built-in%20desk%20and%20shelves.%20If%20it's%20located%20near%20entertaining%20areas%2C%20it%20could%20feature%20a%20built-in%20bar.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221932%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Highland%20Homes'%20Palermo%20floor%20plan.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66f49270f9f6733e4bdfa86a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221102%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHighland%20Homes'%20Palermo%20floor%20plan.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Highland%20Homes%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETake%20a%20floor%20plan%20called%20the%20Palermo%2C%20which%20Highland%20debuted%20in%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20features%20four%20bedrooms%2C%20a%20game%20room%2C%20a%20study%2C%20and%20an%20entertainment%20room.%20This%20floor%20plan%2C%20of%20about%204%2C500%20square%20feet%2C%20can%20cost%20a%20buyer%20from%20about%20%24900%2C000%20to%20%241.3%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Palermo%20floor%20plan%20features%20minimal%20circulation%20space%2C%20with%20rooms%20connected%20directly%20to%20one%20another.%20On%20the%20ground%20floor%2C%20for%20example%2C%20the%20family%20room%20and%20dining%20area%20flow%20into%20the%20kitchen%20and%20breakfast%20nook.%20The%20primary%20suite%20is%20also%20connected%20to%20the%20family%20room.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20a%20hallway%20connects%20bedroom%20four%20to%20a%20game%20room%20upstairs%2C%20the%20builder%20has%20added%20a%20closet%20there%20to%20better%20use%20the%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEliminating%20traditional%20hallways%20in%20home%20design%20maximizes%20usable%20square%20footage%20and%20increases%20efficiency%20by%20allowing%20more%20flexibility%20in%20the%20layout%2C%26quot%3B%20Shurtleff%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22872%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Highland%20Homes'%20271%20floor%20plan.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66fafcbcf44bdb4cfa384856%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22948%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHighland%20Homes'%20271%20floor%20plan.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Highland%20Homes%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20contrast%2C%20a%20Highland%20Homes%20floor%20plan%20from%202018%20for%20a%20one-story%20home%20has%20more%20hallways.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFloor%20plan%20271%20starts%20at%20about%20%24800%2C000%20and%20includes%20four%20bedrooms%2C%20three%20bathrooms%2C%20a%20family%20room%2C%20a%20study%2C%20and%20a%20three-car%20garage.%20It's%20about%202%2C900%20square%20feet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20layout%20features%20an%20entryway%20that%20connects%20to%20a%20vestibule%20leading%20to%20a%20bedroom%20and%20the%20family%20room.%20A%20hallway%20links%20bedrooms%20three%20and%20four%20to%20a%20bathroom%20and%20a%20lifestyle%20room%2C%20while%20another%20leads%20to%20the%20garage%2C%20utility%20room%2C%20and%20mud%20bench.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223dadbf13-adc1-45d2-9e93-fcc67e6b485a%5C%22%3EWhy%20long%20hallways%20are%20becoming%20pass%C3%A9%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20several%20reasons%20hallways%20are%20being%20phased%20out%20of%20newly%20built%20homes%2C%20apart%20from%20saving%20money%20for%20builders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20is%20the%20growing%20popularity%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fliving-multigenerational-home-lessons-pateince-openness-death-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eseveral%20generations%20living%20under%20the%20same%20roof%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gu.org%2Fexplore-our-topics%2Fmultigenerational-households%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%202021%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20nonprofit%20Generations%20United%2C%20more%20than%20one%20in%20four%20Americans%20%E2%80%94%20about%2066.7%20million%20adults%20(18%20and%20above)%20%E2%80%94%20now%20live%20in%20households%20with%20three%20or%20more%20generations%20under%20one%20roof%2C%20a%20271%25%20increase%20from%202011.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYoung%20adults%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fi-live-in-a-multigenerational-household-and-im-not-ashamed-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emoving%20back%20in%20with%20their%20parents%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20graduation%2C%20parents%20are%20living%20with%20their%20adult%20children%20during%20retirement%20(sometimes%20helping%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbabysitting-grandchildren-rewarding-games-spontaneous-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecare%20for%20grandchildren%3C%2Fa%3E)%2C%20and%20siblings%20are%20living%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20response%2C%20many%20architects%20and%20builders%20are%20designing%20floor%20plans%20with%20multigenerational%20households%20in%20mind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221262%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Highland%20Homes'%20608%20floor%20plan.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66f4921df9f6733e4bdfa85e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22828%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHighland%20Homes%20608%20floor%20plan.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Highland%20Homes%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EPictured%20above%20is%20Highland%20Homes'%20608%20floor%20plan%2C%20a%20two-story%20home%20of%20about%204%2C500%20square%20feet%20released%20in%202020.%20It%20costs%20between%20about%20%24900%2C000%20and%20%241.5%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20home's%20entryway%20extends%20from%20the%20front%20door%20to%20the%20dining%20room.%20Along%20this%20path%20are%20the%20study%2C%20a%20curved%20stairway%2C%20the%20first%20garage%2C%20a%20bedroom%2C%20and%20the%20media%20room.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20outdoor%20living%20space%20and%20kitchen%20are%20accessible%20from%20the%20great%20room%2C%20while%20the%20courtyard%20and%20second%20garage%20can%20be%20reached%20through%20the%20kitchen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20really%20not%20any%20hallways%20downstairs%2C%26quot%3B%20Shurtleff%20said.%20%26quot%3BUpstairs%2C%20next%20to%20the%20staircase%2C%20you%20do%20have%20a%20bit%20of%20a%20hallway%20to%20bedroom%20three%2C%20but%20that%20is%20all%20open%20railing%2C%20with%20views%20to%20the%20foyer%20space%20below.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUpstairs%20is%20a%20flexible%20suite%20that%20homeowners%20can%20customize%20based%20on%20what%20they%20need%2C%20whether%20it's%20to%20accommodate%20aging%20parents%20or%20adult%20children.%20This%20suite%2C%20complete%20with%20a%20bathroom%2C%20can%20be%20entered%20directly%20from%20the%20game%20room.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20do%20have%20buyers%20who%20will%20use%20this%20suite%20as%20a%20place%20for%20their%20parents%20to%20stay%2C%20either%20for%20a%20short-%20or%20long-term%20duration%2C%26quot%3B%20Shurtleff%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20also%20have%20buyers%20who%20love%20this%20design%20for%20their%20older%20child%20who%20might%20be%20returning%20home%20from%20college%20before%20starting%20their%20careers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhallways-in-houses-disappearing-new-build-floor-plans-cut-costs-2024-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1728121622000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F670042e4198738e3a70e6d0c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhallways-in-houses-disappearing-new-build-floor-plans-cut-costs-2024-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Today's%20homes%20are%20smaller%20and%20more%20expensive.%20Many%20builders%20are%20eliminating%20hallways%20and%20putting%20the%20square%20footage%20in%20more-used%20parts%20of%20houses.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22alloyd%40insider.com%20(Alcynna%20Lloyd)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhallways-in-houses-disappearing-new-build-floor-plans-cut-costs-2024-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Invasion%20of%20the%20dogs%3A%20How%20surging%20canine%20ownership%20is%20reshaping%20cities%20and%20businesses%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20man%20sits%20at%20a%20bar%20while%20being%20surrounded%20by%20dogs.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66fae58c7518aa57bc9f526c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EJohn%20Tomac%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EPet%20ownership%20is%20on%20the%20rise%2C%20and%20Americans%20are%20spending%20more%20time%20and%20money%20on%20their%20furry%20friends.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EDogs%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20are%20increasingly%20being%20welcomed%20into%20public%20spaces.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThat's%20reshaping%20our%20built%20environment%2C%20from%20bars%20and%20parks%20to%20real%20estate.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EYour%20next%20wedding%20might%20be%20full%20of%20drooling%20guests.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Dog%20Bar%20%E2%80%94%20a%20sprawling%20dog%20venue%20in%20Saint%20Petersburg%2C%20Florida%20%E2%80%94has%20had%20at%20least%20six%20(human)%20proposals%2C%20and%20one%20wedding.%20Some%20of%20the%20couples%20who%20got%20engaged%20met%20at%20the%20dog-catered%20venue%3B%20others%20just%20love%20it%20so%20much%20that%20that's%20where%20they%20wanted%20to%20make%20things%20official.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20just%20romance%20brewing%20at%20the%20Dog%20Bar.%20Politicians%20come%20by%20to%20do%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2FMayorKenWelch%2Fvideos%2Fthanks-for-coming-out-to-support-last-night-at-the-dog-bar-st-pete-99-days-until%2F834832220788817%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esome%20stumping%3C%2Fa%3E%20(and%2C%20presumably%2C%20dog%20petting).%20Young%20professionals%20convene%20for%20meet-ups.%20And%20a%20good%20chunk%20of%20customers%20don't%20even%20have%20dogs%3B%20they%20just%20want%20to%20hang%20out%20amongst%20both%20friends%20human%20and%20furry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20all%20part%20of%20a%20new%20shift%20in%20American%20public%20and%20social%20life%3A%20It's%20gone%20to%20the%20dogs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVirtually%20all%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fshort-reads%2F2023%2F07%2F07%2Fabout-half-us-of-pet-owners-say-their-pets-are-as-much-a-part-of-their-family-as-a-human-member%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUS%20pet%20owners%3C%2Fa%3E%20now%20say%20their%20furry%20companions%20are%20part%20of%20their%20family%20%E2%80%94%20up%20from%2086%25%20of%20dog%20owners%20and%2078%25%20of%20cat%20owners%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fsocial-trends%2F2006%2F03%2F07%2Fgauging-family-intimacy%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ein%202006%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20might%20be%20in%20part%20because%20many%20younger%20Americans%20are%20having%20kids%20later%20than%20previous%20generations%2C%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchild-free-millennials-dont-want-kids-to-hamper-travel-life-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enot%20having%20them%20at%20all%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20are%20really%20combining%20their%20social%20life%20with%20their%20dog%20ownership%20nowadays%2C%26quot%3B%20Kendal%20Kulp%2C%20the%20co-founder%20and%20CEO%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wagbar.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWagbar%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20dog%20park%20and%20bar%20in%20Asheville%2C%20North%20Carolina%2C%20that%20regularly%20hosts%20weddings%2C%20dog%20birthday%20bashes%2C%20and%20Halloween%20parties.%20The%20space%20is%20currently%20hosting%20hurricane%20relief%20efforts%20for%20the%20local%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20feel%20like%20you%20can't%20turn%20a%20corner%20without%20seeing%20a%20four-legged%20friend%2C%20you're%20not%20alone.%20America's%20younger%20workers%20are%20getting%20hooked%20on%20their%20dogs%2C%20and%20they're%20generating%20their%20own%20revenue%20streams%20%E2%80%94%20and%20popping%20up%20everywhere%2C%20occasionally%20to%20some%20people's%20chagrin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20dog%20today%20is%20not%20the%20dog%20of%2010%20years%20ago%2C%26quot%3B%20Bobby%20Boivin%2C%20the%20co-owner%20of%20Boo's%20Dog%20Bar%20in%20Sarasota%2C%20Florida%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20dog%20today%20is%20literally%20a%20child%20in%20the%20family.%20It%20is%20a%20family%20member.%20And%20well%2C%20when%20people%20go%20out%20to%20dinner%2C%20they%20want%20to%20bring%20the%20whole%20family%20with%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20can%20feel%20that%20at%20the%20Dog%20Bar.%20Some%20of%20their%20community%20events%20are%20directly%20inspired%20by%20the%20other%20type%20of%20kids%20%E2%80%94%20the%20human%20variety.%20Stephanie%20Marble%2C%20the%20events%20coordinator%20and%20membership%20director%2C%20said%20she's%20taken%20inspiration%20from%20the%20birthday%20parties%20she%20threw%20for%20her%20sons%20when%20they%20were%20little.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20thing%20that%20we%20do%20that's%20really%20simple%20in%20Florida%20is%20we%20just%20put%20sprinklers%20out%20in%20the%20yard%2C%26quot%3B%20Marble%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bbecause%20in%20the%20summertime%20when%20you're%20trying%20to%20get%20the%20kids%20to%20do%20something%2C%20get%20out%20of%20the%20house%20and%20stop%20complaining%2C%20you%20just%20turn%20the%20sprinkler%20on%20and%20throw%20them%20all%20outside%20in%20the%20front%20yard%20and%20they%20can%20play%20for%20hours%20with%20their%20little%20pools%20and%20their%20little%20sprinklers.%20And%20so%20we%20do%20that%20once%20or%20twice%20a%20year%20at%20Dog%20Bar.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20offers%20party%20packages%2C%20Santa%20for%20holiday%20photos%2C%20and%20an%20Easter%20egg%20hunt%20for%20dogs.%20Santa%20Steve%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20is%20a%20big%20hit%20%E2%80%94%20his%20photos%20with%20dogs%20frequently%20end%20up%20in%20their%20owner's%20digital%20Christmas%20cards.%20He%20has%20almost%20200%20sittings%20with%20dogs%20every%20year%2C%20broken%20up%20across%20two%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20obsession%20with%20canines%20is%20shaping%20our%20built%20environments%2C%20from%20bars%20to%20apartments%20to%20your%20favorite%20coffee%20shop.%20Our%20urban%20infrastructure%20and%20lifestyles%20are%20increasingly%20designed%20around%20pet%20ownership.%20Call%20it%20the%20invasion%20of%20the%20dogs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e6e1611e-a9f7-4ff4-b264-e769292d445a%5C%22%3EEveryone%20got%20dogs%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20a%20single-story%20laundromat%20and%20parking%20lot%20just%20off%20Logan%20Circle%20is%20being%20transformed%20into%20a%206%2C000-square-foot%20%26quot%3Bdog-friendly%20garden%26quot%3B%20called%20Dog%20Daze.%20The%20turf%20and%20tree-dotted%20venue%20will%20feature%20vendors%20serving%20coffee%2C%20beer%2C%20pizza%2C%20smoothies%2C%20and%20acai%20bowls.%20The%20idea%20is%20to%20create%20a%20place%20where%20both%20people%20and%20dogs%20want%20to%20be%20regulars.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20can%20go%20to%20a%20dog%20park%2C%20and%20you%20can%20sit%20down%20for%20a%20quick%20amount%20of%20time%2C%20but%20it's%20really%20more%20of%20a%20check-the-box%20activity%20versus%20actually%20somewhere%20you%20want%20to%20stay%20and%20hang%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Dog%20Daze%20managing%20partner%20Kyle%20Cissel.%20%26quot%3BWe%20wanted%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20it%20was%20somewhere%20they%20felt%20at%20home%2C%20they're%20willing%20to%20spend%20time%2C%20and%20they%20would%20actually%20stay%20for%20longer%20periods%20of%20time%20and%20make%20it%20part%20of%20their%20daily%2C%20weekly%2C%20and%20monthly%20schedule.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20last%20few%20decades%2C%20the%20percentage%20of%20households%20with%20kids%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fshort-reads%2F2021%2F11%2F19%2Fgrowing-share-of-childless-adults-in-u-s-dont-expect-to-ever-have-children%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehas%20plummeted%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20while%20the%20share%20that%20owns%20a%20pet%20has%20ticked%20up.%20The%20percentage%20of%20homebuyers%20with%20a%20child%20under%2018%20living%20with%20them%20has%20fallen%20by%20nearly%20half%20since%20the%201980s%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nar.realtor%2Fblogs%2Feconomists-outlook%2Fa-stunning-stat-for-international-cat-day-there-are-more-american-households-with-pets-than-children%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20NAR%20analysis%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20US%20Census%20data.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20the%20share%20of%20households%20with%20pets%20has%20grown%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Famericanpetproducts.org%2Findustry-trends-and-stats%23%3A~%3Atext%3D2024%2520APPA%2520National%2520Pet%2520Owners%2Ctype%2520and%2520by%2520generational%2520segment.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efrom%2056%25%20in%201988%20to%2066%25%20today%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%20during%20the%20pandemic%20alone%2C%20over%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aspcapro.org%2Fresource%2Fnew-aspca-survey-vast-majority-dogs-and-cats-acquired-during-pandemic-still-their-homes%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E23%20million%20US%20households%3C%2Fa%3E%20welcomed%20dogs%20into%20their%20homes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20see%20dogs%20all%20the%20time%20where%20people%20are%20like%2C%20'Yeah%2C%20this%20is%20my%20covid%20baby.%20I%20never%20liked%20dogs%20before%2C%20but%20I%20got%20one%2C%20and%20now%20it's%20my%20favorite%20thing%20in%20the%20world%2C'%26quot%3B%20said%20Kulp%2C%20of%20Wagbar.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20dog%20boom%20coincided%20with%20a%20few%20other%20key%20trends%3A%20Americans%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmodern-loneliness%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efeeling%20lonely%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20they%20couldn't%20afford%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frising-cost-dating-millennials-gen-z-soaring-cost-love-apps-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esink%20more%20money%20into%20dating%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20larger%20homes%20with%20yards%20were%20financially%20out%20of%20reach.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENearly%20one%20in%20five%20homebuyers%20factor%20pets%20into%20their%20housing%20and%20neighborhood%20choice%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nar.realtor%2Fblogs%2Feconomists-outlook%2Fa-stunning-stat-for-international-cat-day-there-are-more-american-households-with-pets-than-children%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20data%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20National%20Association%20of%20Realtors%20(NAR).%20That's%20up%20from%2015%25%20in%202018.%20Among%20unmarried%20couples%2C%20the%20number%20jumps%20to%2029%25.%20A%20third%20of%20those%20who%20consider%20their%20pets%20needs%20when%20choosing%20a%20home%20say%20they%20want%20to%20be%20close%20to%20parks%20and%20recreation%2C%20NAR%20found.%20Inside%20the%20home%2C%20features%20like%20dog%20and%20cat%20doors%2C%20outdoor%20%26quot%3Bcatios%26quot%3B%20for%20felines%2C%20and%20fenced%20yards%20are%20all%20in%20demand.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20pays%20for%20landlords%20and%20homebuilders%20to%20provide%20for%20their%20non-human%20customers.%20After%20all%2C%20the%20dog%20business%20is%20booming.%20Spending%20on%20US%20pet%20care%20alone%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Famericanpetproducts.org%2Fnews%2Fu.s.-pet-industry-reaches-147-billion-in-sales-in-2023%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehas%20ballooned%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20%2453.3%20billion%20in%202012%20to%20%24147%20billion%20in%202023.%20Americans%20are%20also%20increasingly%20spending%20more%20time%20on%20their%20fuzzy%20friends%3B%20in%202003%2C%20according%20to%20the%20American%20Time%20Use%20Survey%2C%20Americans%20ages%2025%20to%2034%20spent%20just%20over%20four%20minutes%20a%20day%20on%20average%20on%20animal%20and%20pet%20care%20(that%20includes%20Americans%20without%20pets).%20By%202023%2C%20it%20had%20risen%20to%20nine%20minutes%20a%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2Fm5DIk%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Average%20minutes%20spent%20on%20animal%20and%20pet%20care%20among%2025-34%20year%20olds%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22471%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20while%20playgrounds%20have%20traditionally%20been%20a%20social%20hub%20for%20parents%20and%20kids%20alike%2C%20dog%20amenities%20offer%20a%20new%20kind%20of%20community%20or%20third%20place.%20That%20might%20explain%20why%20dog-centric%20bars%20and%20restaurants%20%E2%80%94%20where%20dogs%20aren't%20just%20a%20patio%20feature%20but%20the%20main%20attraction%20%E2%80%94%20are%20popping%20up%20all%20over%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECissel%20thinks%20the%20future%20is%20bright%20for%20dog-friendly%20third%20spaces.%20He%20argued%20that%20a%20dog%20social%20club%20like%20Dog%20Daze%20is%20similar%20to%20a%20local%20gym%20or%20convenience%20store%20%E2%80%94%20an%20amenity%20neighbors%20would%20use%20multiple%20times%20a%20week%2C%20as%20opposed%20to%20other%20leisure%20amenities%20like%20movie%20theaters.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20definitely%20something%20that%20I%20think%20you'll%20see%20in%20every%20neighborhood%20in%20the%20next%2010%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETara%20Downs%2C%20the%20owner%20of%20the%20seven-year-old%20Pub%20Dog%20in%20Colorado%2C%20said%20that%20she's%20noticed%20some%20economic%20shifts%20from%20her%20customers%20%E2%80%94%20three%20or%20four%20years%20ago%2C%20someone%20would%20come%20in%20and%20order%20a%20few%20beers%20and%20food%20for%20themselves%2C%20and%20food%20for%20their%20dogs.%20Now%2C%20they're%20seeing%20humans%20cut%20back%20on%20what%20they're%20spending%20on%20themselves%20but%20still%20getting%20their%20dogs%20the%20same%20treats.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20they're%20still%20finding%20ways%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20they're%20giving%20their%20dogs%20everything%20that%20they%20want%20for%20them%20%E2%80%94%20no%20matter%20what%20it%20means%20for%20them%20in%20the%20human%20sense%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETake%20Fred%20Metzler.%20He%20was%20working%20a%20corporate%20job%20selling%20automatic%20doors%20when%20he%20decided%20he%20wanted%20a%20change.%20After%20adopting%20two%20puppies%2C%20he%20fell%20in%20love%20with%20a%20dog%20bar%20in%20his%20neighborhood.%20He%20and%20his%20former%20business%20partner%20decided%20to%20bring%20that%20concept%20down%20to%20St.%20Petersburg%2C%20Florida%20and%20ended%20up%20opening%20the%20Dog%20Bar%20in%202016.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMetzler%20also%20noticed%20something%20else%20over%20the%20last%20decade%20or%20so%3A%20%26quot%3BThe%20pet%20industry%20seemed%20to%20be%20kind%20of%20recession-proof.%20I%20mean%2C%20through%20'07%2C%20'08%2C%20when%20things%20were%20just%20terrible%2C%20and%20our%20business%20was%20way%20down%20in%20construction%2C%20companies%20like%20PetSmart%20never%20slowed%20down.%26quot%3B%20Even%20in%202009%2C%20PetSmart's%20store%20sales%20growth%20slowed%20down%20to%20what%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2FSB10001424052702304607104579212232612242394%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWall%20Street%20Journal%3C%2Fa%3E%20hailed%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Brespectable%26quot%3B%20rate%20that%20rebounded%20and%20then%20some.%20After%20all%2C%20as%20Kulp%2C%20the%20co-founder%20and%20CEO%20of%20Wagbar%2C%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BPeople%20spend%20more%20money%20on%20their%20dogs%20sometimes%20than%20themselves.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20survey%20from%20the%20American%20Pet%20Products%20Association%20of%2010%2C156%20pet%20owners%20from%20December%202023%20to%20January%202024%2C%2027%25%20of%20dog%20owners%20said%20that%20they%20hold%20holiday%20or%20birthday%20parties%20for%20their%20dogs%20%E2%80%94%20up%20from%20just%2014%25%20in%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20some%20tangible%20ways%2C%20today's%20dog%20owners%20indeed%20see%20their%20pets%20as%20children.%20It%20does%20make%20sense%3A%20In%20a%20country%20where%20the%20cost%20of%20living%20is%20rising%20and%20raising%20a%20kid%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-much-kids-cost-raising-child-inflation-childcare-tax-exemptions-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecosts%20%2426%2C000%20a%20year%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20becoming%20a%20dog%20parent%20might%20feel%20more%20financially%20sound%20%E2%80%94%20and%20still%20help%20stave%20off%20loneliness.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20are%20lonely%2C%20people%20take%20dogs%20as%20serious%20as%20children%2C%26quot%3B%20Luke%20Silverman%2C%20the%20CEO%20and%20co-founder%20of%20Bark%20Social%2C%20a%20social%20club%20for%20dogs%20and%20humans%20with%20locations%20across%20the%20country%2C%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BAll%20that%20together%20brings%20together%20these%20really%20unique%20opportunities%20to%20create%20a%20community.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2220b14fe7-56a0-4109-839f-fcf696ab8d55%5C%22%3EWhat%20it%20means%20to%20have%20dogs%20everywhere%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EStephanie%20Chez%2C%2026%2C%20first%20noticed%20more%20dogs%20around%20when%20she%20spent%20the%20summer%20of%202021%20working%20at%20IKEA.%20Since%20then%2C%20she's%20seen%20them%20everywhere%2C%20from%20Sephora%20to%20Target%20to%20coffee%20shops.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChez%20loves%20dogs%2C%20but%20her%20fiance%20is%20allergic.%20Obviously%2C%20she%20said%2C%20some%20dogs%20are%20service%20animals%20and%20people%20with%20allergies%20will%20have%20to%20contend%20with%20that.%20And%20she%20enjoys%20seeing%20dogs%20around%20%E2%80%94%20but%20she's%20still%20adjusting%20to%20the%20new%20normal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSometimes%20it's%20like%2C%20oh%2C%20did%20you%20have%20to%20bring%20your%20dog%20into%20this%20tiny%20little%20coffee%20shop%3F%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20question%20that%20Americans%20might%20be%20reckoning%20with%20more%2C%20especially%20as%20society%20becomes%20more%20dog-centric.%20According%20to%20the%20APPA%20survey%2C%2015%25%20of%20dog%20owners%20are%20bringing%20their%20dogs%20with%20them%20in%20the%20car%20daily%20to%20run%20errands%20or%20go%20about%20their%20daily%20routines%20%E2%80%94%20up%20from%2010%25%20in%202018.%20More%20dog%20owners%20are%20also%20bringing%20their%20dogs%20with%20them%20on%20vacation%3B%20around%20a%20third%20of%20them%20have%20brought%20their%20dogs%20on%20a%20two-plus%20night%20trip%20via%20car%2C%20and%20around%20a%20fifth%20did%20the%20same%20via%20plane.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20pet%20owners%20might%20be%20looking%20to%20do%20the%20same.%20Silverman%20said%20that%20someone%20once%20called%20and%20asked%20if%20they%20could%20bring%20a%20miniature%20horse%20in.%20His%20answer%3A%20If%20it%20was%20a%20service%20animal%2C%20yes.%20The%20horse%20ultimately%20never%20made%20an%20appearance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnleashed%20Hounds%20and%20Hops%20in%20Minnesota%20has%20had%20one%20cat%20come%20in%20a%20backpack%2C%20according%20to%20founder%20Kevin%20Knutson.%20The%20cat%20mostly%20kept%20to%20itself%3B%20as%20long%20as%20it%20wasn't%20disrupting%20the%20dogs%2C%20it%20was%20okay%20for%20the%20not-dog%20to%20attend.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20the%20same%20thing%20with%20kids%2C%26quot%3B%20Knutson%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20do%20allow%20kids%20at%20our%20facility%20too%2C%20but%20we%20have%20a%20strict%20rule%20about%20they%20have%20to%20stand%20up%20within%20arms%20reach%20of%20an%20adult.%20This%20is%20not%20a%20playground%20for%20kids.%20This%20is%20a%20playground%20for%20dogs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDog%20bars%20are%20also%20increasingly%20becoming%20a%20site%20of%20life's%20big%20moments.%20Multiple%20dog%20bars%20BI%20spoke%20with%20touted%20their%20singles%20events.%20Kulp%20said%20that%20couples%20have%20met%2C%20gotten%20engaged%2C%20and%20even%20gotten%20married%20at%20Wagbar.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20%E2%80%94%20like%20the%20Dog%20Bar%20in%20Florida%20%E2%80%94%20also%20use%20their%20spaces%20as%20a%20neutral%20ground%20for%20dog%20parents%20to%20meet%20adoptable%20dogs%20and%20see%20if%20their%20current%20pups%20get%20along%20with%20a%20potential%20new%20sibling.%20That%20neutral%20stomping%20ground%20has%20also%20made%20it%20a%20good%20space%20for%20broken-up%20dog%20couples%20to%20do%20custody%20hand-offs%3B%20Metzler%20has%20heard%20of%20one%20or%20two%20break-ups%20happening%20there%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20the%20individual%20was%20like%2C%20this%20was%20a%20good-energy%20place.%20My%20partner%20can%20only%20get%20so%20mad%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20as%20dog%20bars%20and%20dog-centric%20spaces%20have%20become%20a%20larger%20part%20of%20life%20for%20many%20Americans%2C%20some%20have%20also%20become%20a%20place%20for%20a%20send-off%20from%20life.%20Kulp%20said%20that%20a%20customer%20in%20his%2080s%20found%20Wagbar%2C%20and%20came%20every%20day%20like%20clockwork.%20When%20he%20passed%20away%2C%20his%20family%20got%20in%20touch%3B%20they'd%20never%20been%20to%20the%20venue%20before%2C%20but%20they%20knew%20what%20a%20big%20impact%20it%20had%20on%20his%20final%20years.%20They%20decided%20to%20hold%20his%20memorial%20there%20%E2%80%94%20with%20dogs%20in%20attendance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20just%20not%20something%20you%20see%20at%20very%20many%20places%20and%20businesses%2C%26quot%3B%20Kulp%20said.%20To%20him%2C%20that's%20a%20testament%20to%20the%20power%20of%20dogs.%20%26quot%3BThey%20just%20are%20a%20catalyst%20for%20that%20connection%20and%20conversation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frise-of-dogs-and-childless-adults-shaping-real-estate-urban-amenities-2024-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1728121322000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66fae5b3f44bdb4cfa383469%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frise-of-dogs-and-childless-adults-shaping-real-estate-urban-amenities-2024-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20growing%20obsession%20with%20canines%20is%20shaping%20our%20built%20environments%2C%20from%20bars%20to%20apartments%20to%20your%20favorite%20coffee%20shop.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.c