nt%20manager%2C%20Doyle%20told%20BI%20he%20thought%20someone%20was%20playing%20a%20practical%20joke%20on%20him.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EStore%20visits%20by%20the%20CEO%20are%20a%20well-established%20tradition%20in%20the%20big%20box%20retail%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20at%20Walmart%2C%20the%20tours%20had%20a%20completely%20different%20complexion%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhistory-of-walmart-2011-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20early%20decades%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20because%20founder%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwalton-family-sam-walmart-stock-billionaires-estate-planning-inheritance-wealth-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESam%20Walton%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20an%20experienced%20pilot%20who%20would%20travel%20the%20country%20in%20a%20small%20private%20plane%2C%20sometimes%20dropping%20out%20of%20the%20sky%20to%20inspect%20his%20stores.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERobert%20Doyle%2C%20now%20a%20store%20manager%20in%20Texas%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20he%20experienced%20such%20a%20visit%20firsthand%20in%20the%201980s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20big%20decade%20for%20the%20Bentonville-based%20retailer%2C%20which%20had%20its%20first%20billion-dollar%20sales%20year%20in%201980%20before%20rocketing%20up%20to%20more%20than%20%2425%20billion%20in%201990%2C%20according%20to%20the%20company's%20annual%20report.%20The%20location%20count%20ballooned%20during%20that%20time%20as%20well%2C%20going%20from%20276%20stores%20to%201%2C402%2C%20with%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.walmartworld.com%2Fcontent%2Fwalmart-world%2Fen_us%2Farticles%2F2022%2F07%2Fgoing-big-memories-from-the-first-supercenter.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efirst%3C%2Fa%3E%20Supercenter%20opening%20in%201988.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221572%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20map%20of%20Walmart%20locations%20from%20the%20company's%201990%20Annual%20Report.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67000e393f2165d716de7aad%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221011%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWalmart%20and%20Sam's%20Club%20stores%20were%20largely%20concentrated%20in%20the%20Southeast%20in%20the%20early%20decades.%3Cp%3EWalmart%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDoyle%20was%20still%20learning%20the%20ropes%20as%20an%20assistant%20manager%20and%20happened%20to%20be%20in%20charge%20of%20the%20store%20one%20day%20while%20his%20boss%20was%20on%20vacation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20phone%20rang.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHey%20Robert%2C%20this%20is%20Sam%2C%26quot%3B%20Doyle%20recalled%20hearing.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20at%20the%20airport%20and%20I'd%20like%20to%20see%20your%20store.%20If%20you%20come%20and%20pick%20us%20up%2C%20we'll%20tour%20your%20store.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDoyle%20says%20he%20first%20thought%20someone%20was%20playing%20a%20practical%20joke%20on%20him%20because%20he%20wasn't%20yet%20familiar%20with%20Walton's%20voice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20quickly%20became%20clear%20that%20it%20was%20indeed%20%26quot%3BMr.%20Sam%26quot%3B%20on%20the%20phone%20and%20that%20someone%20needed%20to%20go%20get%20him%2C%20so%20Doyle%20got%20in%20his%20truck%20and%20hurried%20over.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20arriving%20at%20the%20store%20with%20Walton%2C%20Doyle%20said%20the%20founder%20followed%20a%20well-worn%20routine%20of%20visiting%20the%20service%20desk%20to%20announce%20his%20presence%20over%20the%20P.A.%20speakers%20and%20thank%20customers%20and%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20photograph%20of%20Walmart%20founder%20Sam%20Walton%20speaking%20to%20employees%20is%20displayed%20at%20the%20Walmart%20Museum%20in%20Arkansas.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F670010caa7031864927f816c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221666%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20photo%20of%20Walmart%20founder%20Sam%20Walton%20speaking%20to%20employees%20is%20displayed%20at%20the%20Walmart%20Museum%20in%20Arkansas.%3Cp%3EGilles%20Mingasson%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDoyle%20then%20said%20they%20walked%20the%20store's%20%26quot%3Baction%20alley%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20the%20main%20aisle%20where%20key%20merchandise%20is%20displayed.%20Certain%20items%20at%20Walmart%20are%20designated%20%26quot%3Bvolume%20producing%20items%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20VPIs%2C%20and%20Walton's%20preferred%20VPI%20was%20widely%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2Fwalmartmuseum%2Fposts%2Fwhat-was-sam-waltons-1987-vpi-volume-producing-item%2F3322024011190771%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eknown%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20be%20Moon%20Pies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20always%20had%20to%20have%20a%20Moon%20Pie%20featured%2C%26quot%3B%20Doyle%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20made%20sure%20when%20we%20walked%20by%20to%20show%20him%20his%20VPI.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFollowing%20the%20tour%2C%20Doyle%20said%20Walton%20asked%20that%20the%20store's%20snack%20bar%20be%20opened%20up%20for%20employees%20and%20customers%20to%20have%20popcorn%20and%20soda%20while%20he%20chatted%20with%20the%20store's%20leadership.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20would%20tell%20you%20what%20things%20were%20very%20good%2C%20and%20he%20would%20also%20be%20honest%20about%20things%20that%20were%20an%20opportunity%2C%20like%20we%20need%20to%20fix%20this%2C%26quot%3B%20Doyle%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBack%20at%20the%20airport%2C%20Doyle%20said%20Walton%20asked%20one%20of%20his%20travel%20companions%20for%20cash%20for%20the%20cost%20of%20the%20snacks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20said%2C%20'Here's%20%2450%2C%20that%20should%20cover%20it.%20If%20it%20doesn't%20cover%20it%2C%20you%20call%20me%20and%20let%20me%20know%20how%20much%20more%20I%20owe%20you%2C'%26quot%3B%20Doyle%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20I'm%20like%2C%20'Okay%2C%20sure%2C%20isn't%20it%20your%20company%3F'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%2