.85%20in%201970%20to%2012.72%20in%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDivorcees%20have%20lower%20average%20401(k)%20balances%2C%20less%20savings%2C%20and%20a%20more%20limited%20monthly%20retirement%20income%20than%20married%20people%2C%20according%20to%20a%20Business%20Insider%20analysis%20of%20individual-level%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Edata%20from%20the%20Census%20Bureau's%202023%20Survey%20of%20Income%20and%20Program%20Participation.%20Those%20numbers%20undergird%20the%20reality%20that%20an%20increasing%20number%20of%20middle-aged%20and%20older%20Americans%20are%20facing%3A%20The%20reverberations%20of%20their%20divorces%20will%20be%20felt%20long%20into%20their%20golden%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20retirees%20like%20Mintzer%2C%20this%20can%20leave%20them%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsocial-security-no-savings-snap-benefits-debt-boomers-experiences-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estruggling%20to%20survive%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20cannot%20live%20with%20just%20Social%20Security%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20have%20any%20money%20to%20live%20on.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221bc1fa71-3e75-4a46-9fd2-911ad74fca90%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMost%20married%20couples'%20retirement%20savings%20are%20tied%20together%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20many%20ways%2C%20the%20world%20is%20built%20for%20married%20people%3A%20Taxes%20and%20living%20expenses%20are%20cheaper%20for%20two.%20Married%20couples%20also%20often%20share%20a%20household%20income%2C%20savings%2C%20assets%20like%20real%20estate%20and%20investments%2C%20and%20custody%20if%20they%20have%20children.%20But%20all%20of%20that%20gets%20divided%20up%20in%20a%20divorce.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FlA10J%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Share%20o