hey%20might%20receive%20through%20pensions%2C%20Social%20Security%2C%20retirement%20accounts%2C%20and%20insurance%20benefits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20divorced%20retiree%2C%20however%2C%20takes%20home%20%241%2C940%20a%20month.%20This%20compares%20to%20retirees%20who%20were%20never%20married%20(%241%2C887%20monthly)%2C%20people%20who%20are%20widowed%20(%242%2C381%20monthly)%2C%20and%20people%20who%20remarried%20after%20a%20divorce%20(%242%2C476%20monthly).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2F90yRP%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Monthly%20income%20in%20retirement%20from%20pensions%2C%20retirement%20account%20withdrawals%2C%20life%20insurance%20benefits%2C%20and%20lump%20sum%20pension%20and%20retirement%20account%20income%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22549%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2283554aa9-83be-46d9-a4b9-d01ffdb54708%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWomen%20can%20be%20especially%20vulnerable%20to%20lost%20assets%20and%20savings%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20divorce%20can%20impact%20anyone's%20retirement%20plans%2C%20some%20demographics%20are%20more%20vulnerable%20to%20lost%20assets%20and%20savings.%20For%20example%2C%20Evans%20said%20some%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ewomen%20might%20not%20have%20a%20strong%20financial%20infrastructure%20compared%20to%20men%20%E2%80%94%20women%20couldn't%20have%20their%20own%20credit%20cards%20until%20the%20mid-1970s%2C%20and%20it%20was%20more%20common%20for%20baby%20boomer%20women%20to%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcant-afford-stay-at-home-mom-lifestyle-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estay-at-home-parents%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20hold%20primary%20domestic%20responsibilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEvans%20said%20that%20these%20traditional%20gender%20roles%20could%20contribute%20to%20long-term%20income%20differences.%20America's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpay-gap-by-state-how-much-women-and-men-earn-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egender%20pay%20gap%3C%2Fa%3E%20also%20means%20women%20might%20earn%20less%20than%20men%20for%20the%20same%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20generally%20a%20disparity%20in%20terms%20of%20how%20much%20one%20person%20has%20saved%20into%20a%20retirement%20plan%20versus%20the%20other%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BMaybe%20that's%20because%20one%20spouse%20didn't%20spend%20as%20much%20time%20in%20the%20workforce%2C%20maybe%20they%20helped%20in%20the%20households%20differently.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20whole%2C%20according%20to%20Business%20Insider's%20data%20analysis%2C%20retired%20women's%20finances%20fall%20behind%20men.%20Men's%20monthly%20retirement%20incomes%20are%20nearly%20%24600%20more%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethan%20women's%20%E2%80%94%20%242%2C610%20to%20%242%2C042%20%E2%80%94%20and%20they're%20more%20likely%20to%20have%20a%20balance%20in%20a%20retirement%20account.%20Among%20retirees%20with%20retirement%20accounts%2C%20men%20have%2C%20on%20average%2C%20%24318%2C727%20socked%20away%2C%20regardless%20of%20marriage%20status.%20Women%20have%20%24239%2C706.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKathryn%20Clark%20got%20married%20as%20a%20teenager%20and%20raised%20her%20sons%20in%20California's%20Bay%20Area.%20After%20Clark%20finished%20her%20GED%2C%20she%20worked%20a%20series%20of%20roles%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faccountant-shortage-sexy-taxes-business-school-pwc-kpmg-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccounting%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20healthcare%2C%20and%20tech%20industries%20%E2%80%94%20and%20was%20oftentimes%20the%20main%20household%20income%20earner.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Clark%20finalized%20her%20divorce%20around%20the%20time%20she%20turned%2050%2C%20she%20had%20been%20married%20for%20three%20decades.%20Neither%20she%20nor%20her%20husband%20had%20strong%20retirement%20savings%2C%20and%20they%20sold%20their%20house%20a%20few%20years%20before%20they%20split%20because%20they%20could%20no%20longer%20afford%20it.%20Clark%20didn't%20leave%20the%20relationship%20with%20any%20money%20or%20assets.%20She%20did%2C%20however%2C%20become%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsingle-mom-cant-pay-bills-income-too-high-snap-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esole%20parent%3C%2Fa%3E%20financially%20providing%20for%20their%20children.%20Clark's%20youngest%20son%20was%20still%20a%20teenager%20when%20the%20divorce%20was%20finalized%2C%20and%20she%20had%20to%20spend%20all%20the%20money%20she%20had%20to%20support%20herself%20and%20her%20kids.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20the%20divorce%20came%2C%20I%20had%20nothing%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20just%20walked%20away%20with%20half%20of%20what%20was%20in%20the%20bank%20account%20%E2%80%94%20which%20couldn't%20have%20been%20more%20than%20a%20couple%20hundred%20dollars.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2080%20years%20old%2C%20Clark%20lives%20near%20the%20Bay%20Area%20in%20a%20low-income%20housing%20unit.%20She%20lives%20check%20to%20check%20on%20Social%20Security%2C%20has%20no%20savings%2C%20and%20struggles%20to%20afford%20groceries%20on%20just%20%2423%20a%20month%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbuying-groceries-snap-food-stamps-cant-afford-essentials-credit-card-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESNAP%3C%2Fa%3E.%20When%20Clark's%20ex-husband%20died%20a%20few%20years%20ago%2C%20she%20learned%20that%20she%20could%20receive%20an%20extra%20%24400%20monthly%20based%20on%20his%20Social%20Security%20contributions.%20She%20had%20previously%20been%20trying%20to%20get%20by%20on%20less%20than%20%241%2C000%20a%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOverall%2C%20divorced%20women%20like%20Clark%20see%20lower%20monthly%20retirement%20incomes%20than%20t