mouth%2C%20caused%20by%20a%20stuck%20stick.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%2014-foot-long%20and%202%2C700-pound%20whale%20was%20first%20spotted%20in%202019%20with%20a%20harness%20reading%20%E2%80%9CEquipment%20St.%20Petersburg%E2%80%9D%20fueling%20speculations%20that%20the%20whale%20was%20a%20Russian%20spy.%20This%20prompted%20people%20to%20nickname%20him%20Hvaldimir%2C%20the%20spy%20whale.%20Hvaldimir%20is%20a%20blend%20of%20the%20Norwegian%20word%20for%20whale%2C%20%26quot%3Bhval%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20the%20first%20name%20of%20Russian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20white%20whale%20was%20found%20dead%20outside%20Stavanger%20on%20August%2031.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnimal%20rights%20organizations%20NOAH%20and%20One%20Whale%20claimed%20the%20whale%20had%20been%20shot%20dead%20and%20filed%20a%20police%20report.%20Following%20this%2C%20the%20Veterinary%20Institute%20in%20Sandnes%2C%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20Directorate%20of%20Fisheries%2C%20conducted%20an%20autopsy%20and%20found%20a%2035-centimeter%20(14-inch)%20stick%20lodged%20in%20his%20mouth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20report%20concluded%20that%20the%20probable%20cause%20of%20death%20was%20a%20bacterial%20infection%2C%20possibly%20a%20result%20of%20wounds%20in%20his%20mouth%20caused%20by%20a%20stick%20that%20got%20stuck%2C%E2%80%9D%20Amund%20Preede%20Revheim%2C%20Norway%20police%20official%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CPinnen%20(Norwegian%20word%20for%20peg%2C%20a%20wooden%20stick)%20may%20also%20have%20led%20to%20Hvaldimir%20having%20challenges%20with%20its%20nutrition%2C%20thus%20increasing%20infections%2C%E2%80%9D%20stated%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politiet.no%2Faktuelt-tall-og-fakta%2Faktuelt%2Fnyheter%2F2024%2F10%2F04%2Fsor---vest-oppdatering-hvaldimir-endelig-obduksjonsrapport-er-klar%2F%5C%22%3Epress%20release%3C%2Fa%3E%20issued%20by%20Norway%20police.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAssessment%20done%20by%20the%20Veterinary%20Institute%20and%20police%20criminal%20technicians%20found%20that%20there%20was%20no%20injury.%20X-ray%20of%20the%20chest%20and%20head%20can%20be%20conducted%20without%20the%20presence%20of%20a%20projector%20or%20other%20metal%20fragments%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20police%20didn't%20find%20any%20trace%20of%20bullets%20and%20therefore%2C%20no%20further%20investigation%20was%20done.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20are%20no%20investigations%20that%20indicate%20that%20Hvaldimir%20is%20living%20illegally.%20The%20police%20therefore%20had%20no%20reason%20to%20launch%20an%20investigation%20into%20the%20whale's%20death%2C%20and%20responded%20to%20the%20incoming%20report%E2%80%9D%2C%20said%20Preed%20Revheim.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20biosecurity%20reasons%2C%20remains%20are%20usually%20destroyed%20after%20autopsies%20at%20the%20Veterinary%20Institute.%20In%20this%20case%2C%20the%20Directorate%20of%20Fisheries%20has%20decided%20to%20donate%20the%20skeleton%20of%20the%20white%20whale%20Hvaldimir%20to%20the%20Nature%20Museum%20and%20Botanical%20Garden%20at%20UiA%20University%20in%20Agder.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20Norway%20requested%20its%20citizens%20to%20avoid%20any%20contact%20with%20Hvaldimir%20who%20was%20seen%20in%20a%20fjord%20close%20to%20Oslo.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1728100860000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-09%2Fpvlb0bmo_spy-whale-_625x300_01_September_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fcelebrated-russian-spy-whale-hvaldimir-did-not-die-of-gunshot-wounds-6720033%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20beluga%20whale%20%26quot%3BHvaldimir%26quot%3B%2C%20found%20dead%20in%20Norway%20in%20August%2C%20was%20not%20shot%20to%20death%20as%20claimed%20by%20animal%20rights%20groups%20but%20died%20of%20bacterial%20infection%2C%20said%20Norwegian%20Police.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22